It gives full control over commit history.
Command: git rebase -i HEAD~n: where n is no. of commits to edit
•	Common Interactive Rebase Commands:
•	Pick: keep the commit as it is
•	Reword: change the commit message
•	Edit: modify the commit
•	Squash: Combine commit with previous commit
•	Fixup: combine commit and discard its message
•	Drop: remove the commit
1.	Pick: pick abc123 Add Login
default option(commit remains unchanged) 
2. Reword: reword abc123 Add Login
     Git asks to edit only commit message
3. Edit: edit abc123 Add Login
Git pauses at the commit. You can modify files, add changes, amend commit then continue: 
git rebase --continue
4.Squash: is ised to combine multiple consecutive commits into a single commit
So you have to keep first one as pick rest commits to combine this as squash 
Example : -pick abc123 Add login
	   -squash abc124 add button in login
	   -squash abc125 added bg-color to login page
•	All three gets combined and after saving it asks to rewrite combined commit message you can write it as : “Added login page with  bg-color and buttons”
•	Never squash or rebase commits that have already been pushed to a remote repository
•	If you make a mistake or get stuck in a complex merge conflict during a rebase, you can always safely cancel the entire operation and return to your original state by running git rebase --abort
5.	Fixup: Similar to squash
Squash - combine code+combine titles: opens editor to rewrite titles of commits
Fixup - combine code+ delete extra titles: git automatically deletes the titles of extra commits and keeps only the first commit’s title you don’t need to type anything
Command		 Merge codes?	Asks to edit message
Squash			yes			yes(opens editor)
Fixup 				yes			 no(deletes extra titles)
6.	Drop: drop abc123  Debug code
Remove unwanted commits(commit disappears)
•	Commands:
•	Start interactive rebase: git rebase -i HEAD~3
•	Continue: git rebase --continue
•	Abort: git rebase --abort
•	Skip commit: git rebase --skip
Avoid using rebase after pushing as it confuses others.

